    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Aloo Tikki is a crispy North Indian street food made from mashed potatoes, spices, and herbs. It's shallow-fried until golden and served hot with chutneys.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>20 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>3 medium potatoes (boiled & mashed)</li>
        <li>1 green chili (finely chopped)</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp red chili powder</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp garam masala</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp dry mango powder (amchur)</li>
        <li>2 tbsp chopped coriander</li>
        <li>2 tbsp cornflour or breadcrumbs</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>Oil for shallow frying</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>In a bowl, combine mashed potatoes, spices, coriander, salt, and cornflour. Mix well.</li>
        <li>Shape into small round tikkis and flatten slightly.</li>
        <li>Heat oil in a pan. Place tikkis and shallow-fry on medium heat.</li>
        <li>Flip when one side is golden and crispy. Cook the other side similarly.</li>
        <li>Serve hot with green chutney or tamarind sauce.</li>
    </ol>
